# GitChangeActivityReport Local Rules

## Overview

This folder contains scripts for generating Git change activity reports across multiple repositories.

**Main Script:** `New-GitChangeActivityReport.ps1`

---

## Standards

### Default Exclusions

Exclude downloaded/generated/vendor/build/runtime folders from reporting and totals:
- `bin`, `obj`, `node_modules`, `dist`, `build`
- `runtimes`, `site-packages`, `venv`, `.venv`
- `__pycache__`, `.pytest_cache`
- Any path containing `_old`

### Report Format

**Compact overview report (default):**
- Per-repo summary with max ~10 lines per repo
- No individual file listings
- Summarize "value added" using commit subjects (offline heuristics)
- Keep code vs documentation metrics separate

### Author Matching

✅ **PREFERRED:** Email addresses (shorter, more reliable)
```powershell
-Authors "geir.helge.starholm@Dedge.no"
```

❌ **AVOID:** Display names (vary across repos)
```powershell
-Authors "Geir Starholm"  # May not match all commits
```

**Multiple authors:** Comma-separated
```powershell
-Authors "email1@domain.com,email2@domain.com"
```

### FKGEISTA Secondary Email

When generating a report for FKGEISTA, the script automatically includes `geir@starholm.net` in the Authors list to improve matching across repos with different author configurations.

This only happens when:
- Current user is FKGEISTA
- Primary email (`geir.helge.starholm@Dedge.no`) is in Authors list

---

## Parameters

| Parameter | Default | Description |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| `-Root` | `C:\opt\src` | Root directory to scan for git repos |
| `-DaysBack` | `21` | Days to look back |
| `-Authors` | Current user | Comma-separated email addresses |
| `-FromDate` | - | Start date (YYYY-MM-DD) |
| `-ToDate` | - | End date (YYYY-MM-DD) |
| `-Compact` | `$true` | Compact format (no file listings) |
| `-Detailed` | - | Full file-by-file listing |
| `-WriteJson` | - | Also write JSON output |
| `-VerifyTotals` | - | Verify totals against git |
| `-SendEmail` | - | Send report via email |
| `-SendSms` | - | Send summary via SMS |

---

## Notifications

If the user requests it, the report script may send:
- **Email**: Using `Send-Email` (GlobalFunctions) with the report attached
- **SMS**: Using `Send-Sms` (GlobalFunctions) with a short "report ready" message

---

## Output Files

- `change_activity_report_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.md` - Markdown report
- `change_activity_report_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.json` - JSON data (if `-WriteJson`)
- `change_activity_report_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.AI_SUMMARY.md` - AI summary (if generated)

---

## Quick Usage

```powershell
# Default: Last 21 days, current user, compact format
.\New-GitChangeActivityReport.ps1 -Compact -VerifyTotals

# Specific author and time period
.\New-GitChangeActivityReport.ps1 `
    -Authors "svein.morten.erikstad@Dedge.no" `
    -DaysBack 14 -Compact -VerifyTotals -SendSms

# Date range with email notification
.\New-GitChangeActivityReport.ps1 `
    -Authors "email1@domain.com,email2@domain.com" `
    -FromDate "2025-12-01" -ToDate "2025-12-18" `
    -Compact -WriteJson -SendEmail
```
